The Chronicle Innocent Kurira, Sports Reporter THE Bulawayo Basketball League is returning to action this coming weekend after a month long festive break.
Bulawayo Basketball Association (BBA) secretary general Francis Dube said they are ready to resume games. “We expect to resume the league campaign this Saturday. There are teams yet to fully affiliate and we hope they are working on that. We are really excited and looking forward to a successful second half campaign,” said Dube.
At the break, Legends were on top of the table having accumulated 14 points from seven games. <img class="wp-image-654054 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/10/Bulawayo-Basketball-Association-BBA-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/10/Bulawayo-Basketball-Association-BBA-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/10/Bulawayo-Basketball-Association-BBA-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Bulawayo Basketball Association They won all their seven games. Southern Mavericks are in second position with 11 points from the same number of games.
Lakers and Giants are third and fourth on the table respectively, tied on 10 points. In the women’s division, Lakers Mzansi had managed to get 10 points from five games which places them top of the table. Angels are in second place.
Bulawayo are also preparing to host the Afro-Basket Zone Six qualifiers and Afro Can.  The two competitions will see the women’s and men senior national teams return to action after what has been a long hiatus.
Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, Angola, South Africa, Lesotho, Botswana and hosts Zimbabwe are participating in the competitions which will run from February 20-28. <img class="wp-image-606831 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Untitled-5-3.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Untitled-5-3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Untitled-5-3-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> imbabwe International Trade Fair (ZITF) The games will be at the Zimbabwe International Trade Fair (ZITF). – @innocentskizoe